Date: Wed 24 Jul 2002
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@vet.gla.ac.uk>
Source: Times of India, via Newsline, Tue 23 Jul 2002 [edited]

India: Dengue Fever Outbreak in West Bengal
-------------------------------------------
The people of West Midnapores, Salboni and Garbeta have been
afflicted with classical dengue fever, according to an investigation of
the Burdwan Medical College Hospital BMCH. The Principal of BMCH,
Dr Bijoy Mukherji, has sent the findings to Dr Chittaranjan Maity,
director of medical education in West Bengal.
The first attack was reported at Garbeta on 2 Jun 2002. [As of Wed 24
Jul 2002], the number of affected people in Salboni was 840, of whom
3 have died. Blood samples will also be sent to the National Institute of
Cholera and Enteric Diseases, said Mukherji. On Monday and
Wednesday, a team collected blood samples from victims. The victims
homes were infested with _Aedes_ mosquitoes, the carrier of dengue.
