Date: Sat 27 Jul 2002
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: Philippine Daily Enquirer, Fri 26 Jul 2002 [edited]

Philippines: Dengue Fever Deaths in Bicol Region
------------------------------------------------------
Dengue fever has killed at least 7 patients and hospitalized 128 persons
in 6 months in the Bicol Region. Department of Health (DOH)
epidemiologist chief in Bicol Dr. Ferchito Avelino said that from
January to July 2002, 7 have died of dengue, 6 of them from Albay and
one from Catanduanes. Avelino added that there had been 4 unreported
cases of dengue fever in Masbate last month. He believed that there are
more unreported dengue cases, especially those confined in private
hospitals.
At least 54 dengue cases were recorded by the Provincial Health Office
(PHO) during the first 6 months of the year, prompting the office to
intensify its information and education campaign on the disease.
Polangui has the highest record of cases with 12. DOH regional director
Gerardo Bayugo has sought the cooperation of local government units
in improving its sanitation campaign to prevent a dengue outbreak.
Breeding areas of mosquito would multiply rapidly this rainy season if
no preventive measures are taken, he warned.
[Byline: Job Belen and Melanie J. Valenciano]
